history.text: Did you have a good weekend? We had a nice time, watched a movie.
You should check out The Social Network it stars Jesse Eisenberg and Eduardo Saverin
I had a great weekend went and saw 3 movies at the theater.
I hadn't heard about that one. What is it about?
The Social Network is based on a book called The Accidnetal Bioolnaires.   The Founding of Facebook.
Oh cool. That sounds good. Is it boring just like a guy sitting in his dorm coding on the computer?
No it's not boring at all.   It also has Justin Timberlake in it. They have a good story, historically accurate but entertaining.
I love Justin Timberlake, I think he's great. So, the movie is historically accurate? Is there action to it?
Well no I wouldn't say action. It's a drama. It really is good got a average of 9/10 on rotten tomatoes.
That's a great review. What character does Justin Timberlake play?
Sean Parker the inventor of a online music streaming service.
Interesting. I didn't realize that an online music streaming service
Well that's justin's character has little to nothing to actually do with facebook.
